headline: Rollins (NYSE:ROL) Exceeds Q2 Expectations
summary: Pest control company Rollins (NYSE:ROL) reported Q2 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 12.1% year on year to $999.5 million. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.30 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Rollins (ROL) Q2 Earnings and Revenues Surpass Estimates
summary: Rollins (ROL) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of +3.45% and +2.05%, respectively, for the quarter ended June 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Rollins: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: ATLANTA (AP) — Rollins Inc. ROL) on Wednesday reported second-quarter profit of $141.5 million. The Atlanta-based company said it had profit of 29 cents per share.

headline: Rollins (ROL) Board Declares Regular US$0.17 Dividend for September Payout
summary: Rollins (ROL) affirmed a quarterly dividend of $0.165 per share, reflecting its dedication to shareholder value. Despite a modest 1% price increase in the last quarter, this was in line with broader market trends, which rose by 1% over the same period, suggesting the dividend affirmation had a neutral effect.
